```

## Testing Subscriptions

```ts
it("cancels previous subscription with switchMap", fakeAsync(() => {
  service.search("ab");
  tick(300);
  const req1 = httpMock.expectOne("/api/search?q=ab");

  service.search("abc"); // should cancel req1
  tick(300);
  const req2 = httpMock.expectOne("/api/search?q=abc");

  req2.flush([{ name: "Result" }]);
  expect(req1.cancelled).toBe(true);
}));
```

## Conventions

- Use `TestBed.inject` to get service instance
- `HttpClientTestingModule` for HTTP mocking
- `httpMock.verify()` in `afterEach` to ensure no pending requests
- `fakeAsync` + `tick` for testing temporal operators (debounce, delay)
- Test state sequences (loading -> success / error)
- Verify subscription cancellation
